<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Flex Gateway Policies - Comprehensive Guide</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="common-styles.css">
    <style>
        .policy-tabs {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #0066cc;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .tab-btn {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8f9fa, #e9ecef);
            border: 2px solid #dee2e6;
            border-radius: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: #495057;
        }

        .tab-btn:hover {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e9ecef, #dee2e6);
            border-color: #0066cc;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }

        .tab-btn.active {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0066cc, #004499);
            color: white;
            border-color: #0066cc;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 102, 204, 0.3);
        }

        .policy-content {
            display: none;
            animation: fadeIn 0.5s ease-in;
        }

        .policy-content.active {
            display: block;
        }

        .policy-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(600px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .policy-card {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffffff, #f8f9fa);
            border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .policy-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        }

        .policy-card h3 {
            color: #0066cc;
            margin-top: 0;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            font-size: 1.3em;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #e9ecef;
            padding-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .yaml-block {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d3748, #1a202c);
            border: 1px solid #4a5568;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 15px;
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 13px;
            color: #e2e8f0;
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 15px 0;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            position: relative;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .yaml-block:hover {
            border-color: #0066cc;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 102, 204, 0.3);
        }

        .yaml-block::before {
            content: "📋 Double-click to copy";
            position: absolute;
            top: 5px;
            right: 10px;
            font-size: 10px;
            color: #a0aec0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        .deployment-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(500px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .config-example {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff3cd, #ffeaa7);
            border: 1px solid #ffeeba;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 15px 0;
        }

        .config-example h4 {
            margin-top: 0;
            color: #856404;
        }

        .footer {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0066cc, #004499);
            color: white;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 40px;
        }

        .footer h3 {
            margin-top: 0;
            font-size: 1.5em;
        }

        @keyframes fadeIn {
            from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
            to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .policy-grid, .deployment-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
            
            .tab-btn {
                padding: 8px 16px;
                font-size: 14px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>🛡️ Comprehensive Flex Gateway Policies Guide</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Production-Ready YAML Configurations for Enterprise Security & Compliance</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav class="navbar">
        <div class="nav-container">
            <a href="index.html" class="nav-brand">
                <span>🚀</span> Employee Onboarding Platform
            </a>
            <div class="nav-toggle" onclick="toggleMobileMenu()">
                <span></span>
                <span></span>
                <span></span>
            </div>
            <ul class="nav-menu" id="navMenu">
                <li><a href="index.html" class="nav-link">Overview</a></li>
                <li><a href="02-Enhanced-Navigation.html" class="nav-link">Navigation</a></li>
                <li><a href="03-Flex-Gateway-Policies.html" class="nav-link">Flex Gateway</a></li>
                <li><a href="04-RTF-EKS-Setup.html" class="nav-link">RTF EKS</a></li>
                <li><a href="05-Anypoint-Platform.html" class="nav-link">Anypoint</a></li>
                <li><a href="06-Auto-scaling.html" class="nav-link">Auto-scaling</a></li>
                <li><a href="07-HIPAA-Compliance.html" class="nav-link">HIPAA</a></li>
                <li><a href="08-RTF-Azure-Installation.html" class="nav-link">RTF Azure</a></li>
                <li><a href="09-RTF-AWS-Installation.html" class="nav-link">RTF AWS</a></li>
                <li><a href="10-RTF-Security.html" class="nav-link">Security</a></li>
                <li><a href="11-Logging-Monitoring.html" class="nav-link">Monitoring</a></li>
                <li><a href="12-Capacity-Planning.html" class="nav-link">Capacity Planning</a></li>
                <li><a href="13-MuleSoft-Capacity-Planning.html" class="nav-link">MuleSoft Planning</a></li>
                <li><a href="14-Azure-AWS-RTF-Capacity-Planning.html" class="nav-link">Cloud RTF Planning</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>🎯 Policy Categories</h2>
            <p>Flex Gateway provides a comprehensive set of policies to secure, manage, and monitor your APIs. Each policy can be applied individually or combined for layered security approaches.</p>

            <div class="policy-tabs">
                <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="showPolicyCategory('security')">🔒 Security Policies</button>
                <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showPolicyCategory('auth')">🔐 Authentication</button>
                <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showPolicyCategory('traffic')">🚦 Traffic Management</button>
                <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showPolicyCategory('transform')">🔄 Transformation</button>
                <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showPolicyCategory('monitoring')">📊 Monitoring & Analytics</button>
                <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showPolicyCategory('compliance')">⚖️ Compliance</button>
            </div>

            <!-- Security Policies -->
            <div id="security" class="policy-content active">
                <h3>🔒 Security Policies</h3>
                
                <div class="policy-grid">
                    <!-- CORS Policy -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS)</h3>
                        <p>Controls cross-origin requests and manages CORS headers for browser security.</p>
                        
                        <div class="config-example">
                            <strong>Configuration Features:</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Allowed origins, methods, and headers</li>
                                <li>Credentials support</li>
                                <li>Preflight request handling</li>
                                <li>Max age for preflight caching</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: cors-policy
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: cors
  config:
    "allowedOrigins":
      - "https://employee-portal.company.com"
      - "https://admin.company.com"
      - "http://localhost:3000"
    "allowedMethods":
      - GET
      - POST
      - PUT
      - DELETE
      - OPTIONS
    "allowedHeaders":
      - "Content-Type"
      - "Authorization"
      - "X-API-Key"
      - "X-Request-ID"
    "exposedHeaders":
      - "X-Total-Count"
      - "X-RateLimit-Remaining"
    "allowCredentials": true
    "maxAge": 3600
    "optionsPassthrough": false</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- IP Allowlist/Blocklist -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>IP Allowlist & Blocklist</h3>
                        <p>Controls access based on client IP addresses with support for CIDR ranges.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: ip-filtering
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: ip-allowlist
  config:
    "allowedIPs":
      - "192.168.1.0/24"     # Corporate network
      - "10.0.0.0/16"        # VPN range
      - "203.0.113.0/24"     # Partner network
    "deniedIPs":
      - "192.168.1.100"      # Specific blocked IP
      - "10.0.0.50/32"       # Another blocked IP
    headerName: "X-Forwarded-For"  # For load balancer scenarios
    "trustProxy": true</div>

                        <div class="yaml-block"># IP Blocklist Configuration
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: ip-blocklist
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: public-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: ip-blocklist
  config:
    "blockedIPs":
      - "203.0.113.0/24"
      - "198.51.100.0/24"
    headerName: "X-Real-IP"
    "trustProxy": true</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- TLS Policy -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>TLS/SSL Configuration</h3>
                        <p>Enforces HTTPS connections and configures TLS settings for secure communication.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: Gateway
metadata:
  name: secure-gateway
  namespace: default
spec:
  gatewayClassName: flex
  listeners:
  - name: https
    port: 443
    protocol: HTTPS
    tls:
      mode: Terminate
      certificateRefs:
      - name: employee-onboarding-tls
        kind: Secret
  - name: http-redirect
    port: 80
    protocol: HTTP
    allowedRoutes:
      namespaces:
        from: All

---
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: tls-policy
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: secure-gateway
    kind: Gateway
  policyRef:
    name: tls
  config:
    "requireTLS": true
    minVersion: "1.2"
    "cipherSuites":
      - "TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384"
      - "TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256"
    "redirectToHTTPS": true</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Header Injection/Removal -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Header Injection & Removal</h3>
                        <p>Adds security headers and removes sensitive information from requests/responses.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: header-injection
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: header-injection
  config:
    "inboundHeaders":
      - name: "X-Forwarded-Proto"
        value: "https"
        "overwrite": true
      - name: "X-Request-ID"
        value: "${uuid()}"
        "overwrite": false
    "outboundHeaders":
      - name: "X-Content-Type-Options"
        value: "nosniff"
        "overwrite": true
      - name: "X-Frame-Options"
        value: "DENY"
        "overwrite": true
      - name: "Strict-Transport-Security"
        value: "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains"
        "overwrite": true
      - name: "X-XSS-Protection"
        value: "1; mode=block"
        "overwrite": true
    "removeHeaders":
      - "Server"
      - "X-Powered-By"
      - "X-AspNet-Version"</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Authentication Policies -->
            <div id="auth" class="policy-content">
                <h3>🔐 Authentication Policies</h3>
                
                <div class="policy-grid">
                    <!-- JWT Validation -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>JWT Validation</h3>
                        <p>Validates JSON Web Tokens with support for multiple providers and custom claims.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: jwt-validation
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: jwt-validation
  config:
    "jwtKeyOrigin": jwks
    jwksUrl: "https://auth.employee-portal.com/.well-known/jwks.json"
    "jwksServiceTimeToLive": 300
    audience: "employee-onboarding-api"
    issuer: "https://auth.employee-portal.com/"
    "validateAudience": true
    "validateIssuer": true
    "validateExp": true
    "validateNbf": true
    "clockSkew": 60
    "mandatoryClaims":
      - "sub"
      - "iat"
      - "exp"
      - "employee_role"
    "customValidations":
      - expression: "#[payload.employee_role != null]"
        errorMessage: "Missing employee role"
      - expression: "#[payload.department != null]"
        errorMessage: "Missing department information"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- OAuth 2.0 -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>OAuth 2.0 Token Enforcement</h3>
                        <p>Enforces OAuth 2.0 access tokens with introspection and scope validation.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: oauth2-enforcement
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: oauth2-enforcement
  config:
    introspectionUrl: "https://oauth.company.com/introspect"
    clientId: "flex-gateway-client"
    clientSecret: "${secure::oauth.client.secret}"
    "requiredScopes":
      - "employee:read"
      - "employee:write"
      - "onboarding:manage"
    scopeValidationCriteria: "containsAll"
    "cacheConfiguration":
      "enabled": true
      entryTtl: 300
      maxEntries: 1000
    "customHeaders":
      - name: "X-User-ID"
        value: "#[payload.sub]"
      - name: "X-User-Scopes"
        value: "#[payload.scope]"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Basic Authentication -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Basic Authentication</h3>
                        <p>Simple username/password authentication with LDAP integration support.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: basic-auth
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: admin-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: basic-auth-simple
  config:
    users:
      - username: "admin"
        password: "${secure::admin.password}"
      - username: "support"
        password: "${secure::support.password}"

---
# LDAP-based Basic Auth
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: basic-auth-ldap
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: basic-auth-ldap
  config:
    ldapConfig:
      url: "ldaps://ldap.company.com:636"
      baseDn: "ou=employees,dc=company,dc=com"
      userSearchBase: "ou=users"
      userSearchFilter: "(uid={0})"
      bindDn: "cn=service,ou=services,dc=company,dc=com"
      bindPassword: "${secure::ldap.bind.password}"
      connectionTimeout: 30000
      responseTimeout: 60000</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- API Key Authentication -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>API Key Authentication</h3>
                        <p>API key-based authentication with flexible key placement and validation.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: api-key-auth
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: public-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: api-key-authentication
  config:
    credentialOrigin: customExpression
    credentialExpression: "#[attributes.headers['X-API-Key']]"
    keys:
      - key: "pk_live_abc123def456"
        name: "Production Client"
        permissions:
          - "read"
          - "write"
      - key: "pk_test_xyz789uvw012"
        name: "Test Client"
        permissions:
          - "read"
    rateLimitByKey: true
    keyRotationEnabled: true

---
# Query Parameter API Key
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: api-key-query
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: webhook-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: api-key-authentication
  config:
    credentialOrigin: queryParam
    queryParamName: "api_key"
    keys:
      - key: "webhook_key_123"
        name: "Webhook Client"</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Traffic Management -->
            <div id="traffic" class="policy-content">
                <h3>🚦 Traffic Management Policies</h3>
                
                <div class="policy-grid">
                    <!-- Rate Limiting -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Rate Limiting</h3>
                        <p>Controls API usage with sophisticated rate limiting algorithms and quotas.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: rate-limiting
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: rate-limiting
  config:
    "rateLimits":
      - maximumRequests: 1000
        "timePeriod": 1
        "timePeriodTimeUnit": MINUTE
        identifier: "#[attributes.headers['client-id']]"
        "keyResolver": customExpression
      - maximumRequests: 100
        "timePeriod": 1
        "timePeriodTimeUnit": MINUTE
        identifier: "#[attributes.remoteAddress]"
        "keyResolver": clientIpExpression
    "quotas":
      - maximumRequests: 50000
        "timePeriod": 1
        "timePeriodTimeUnit": DAY
        identifier: "#[attributes.headers['client-id']]"
    "algorithm": slidingWindow
    "distributeQuota": true
    "exposeHeaders": true
    "headersConfiguration":
      - name: "X-RateLimit-Limit"
      - name: "X-RateLimit-Remaining"
      - name: "X-RateLimit-Reset"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Spike Control -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Spike Control</h3>
                        <p>Protects against traffic spikes and sudden load increases with queuing mechanisms.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: spike-control
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: spike-control
  config:
    "maximumRequests": 500
    timePeriodInMilliseconds: 1000
    "queuingRequestTimeout": 5000
    "delayTimeInMillis": 100
    "delayAttempts": 3
    "algorithm": slidingWindow
    keySelector: "#[attributes.headers['client-id']]"
    "exposeHeaders": true</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Circuit Breaker -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Circuit Breaker</h3>
                        <p>Prevents cascade failures by monitoring downstream service health and failing fast.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: circuit-breaker
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-service
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: circuit-breaker
  config:
    "onErrorContinue": false
    "failureThreshold": 5
    "successThreshold": 2
    "timeout": 60000
    "delay": 5000
    "tripOnTimeouts": true
    "tripOnConnectFailure": true
    "trip5xx": true
    "trip4xx": false
    "customErrorStatuses":
      - 503
      - 504
    "fallbackResponse":
      "statusCode": 503
      "body": |
        {
          "error": "Service temporarily unavailable",
          "message": "The employee service is currently experiencing issues. Please try again later.",
          "timestamp": "${now()}"
        }
      "headers":
        Content-Type: "application/json"
        Retry-After: "60"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Load Balancing -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Load Balancing</h3>
                        <p>Distributes traffic across multiple backend services with health checking.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: HTTPRoute
metadata:
  name: load-balanced-api
  namespace: default
spec:
  parentRefs:
  - name: employee-gateway
  rules:
  - matches:
    - path:
        type: PathPrefix
        value: /api/employees
    backendRefs:
    - name: employee-service-1
      port: 80
      weight: 50
    - name: employee-service-2
      port: 80
      weight: 30
    - name: employee-service-3
      port: 80
      weight: 20

---
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: load-balancer-policy
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: load-balanced-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: load-balancer
  config:
    "algorithm": roundRobin  # Options: roundRobin, leastConnections, weightedRandom
    "healthCheck":
      "enabled": true
      "interval": 30
      "timeout": 10
      path: "/health"
      "expectedStatus": 200
      "unhealthyThreshold": 3
      "healthyThreshold": 2
    stickySession:
      "enabled": true
      cookieName: "LB_SESSION"
      cookiePath: "/"
      "cookieSecure": true</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Transformation Policies -->
            <div id="transform" class="policy-content">
                <h3>🔄 Transformation Policies</h3>
                
                <div class="policy-grid">
                    <!-- Message Logging -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Message Logging</h3>
                        <p>Logs request/response messages with configurable detail levels and PII protection.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: message-logging
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: message-logging
  config:
    level: INFO
    logRequest: true
    logResponse: true
    logHeaders: true
    logPayload: true
    maxPayloadSize: 10240
    category: "flex.gateway.employee.api"
    beforeCall:
      "enabled": true
      message: "Processing employee onboarding request"
      includeHeaders:
        - "X-Request-ID"
        - "User-Agent"
        - "Content-Type"
      "excludeHeaders":
        - "Authorization"
        - "Cookie"
    afterCall:
      "enabled": true
      message: "Employee onboarding request completed"
      logDuration: true
    piiProtection:
      "enabled": true
      maskFields:
        - "ssn"
        - "password"
        - "creditCard"
      maskPattern: "***MASKED***"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- JSON Threat Protection -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>JSON Threat Protection</h3>
                        <p>Protects against JSON-based attacks by validating structure and content limits.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: json-threat-protection
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: json-threat-protection
  config:
    "maxArrayElementCount": 1000
    "maxContainerDepth": 10
    "maxObjectEntryCount": 100
    "maxObjectEntryNameLength": 256
    "maxStringValueLength": 10000
    "maxDocumentLength": 1048576
    "allowComments": false
    "allowDuplicateKeys": false
    "strictValidation": true
    errorResponse:
      "statusCode": 400
      "body": |
        {
          "error": "Invalid JSON payload",
          "message": "The provided JSON payload violates security constraints",
          "timestamp": "${now()}"
        }</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- XML Threat Protection -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>XML Threat Protection</h3>
                        <p>Validates XML payloads against various XML-based security threats and structure limits.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: xml-threat-protection
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: legacy-soap-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: xml-threat-protection
  config:
    maxElementCount: 1000
    maxAttributeCount: 100
    maxAttributeNameLength: 256
    maxAttributeValueLength: 1000
    maxElementNameLength: 256
    maxElementValueLength: 10000
    "maxDocumentLength": 1048576
    maxChildrenPerElement: 100
    maxDepth: 10
    "allowComments": false
    allowProcessingInstructions: false
    allowDtd: false
    allowExternalEntities: false
    errorResponse:
      "statusCode": 400
      "body": |
        <error>
          <code>400</code>
          <message>Invalid XML payload</message>
          <description>The provided XML payload violates security constraints</description>
          <timestamp>${now()}</timestamp>
        </error></div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Request/Response Transformation -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>DataWeave Transformation</h3>
                        <p>Transforms request and response payloads using DataWeave expressions.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: dataweave-transformation
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: dataweave-transformation
  config:
    requestTransformation:
      "enabled": true
      "expression": |
        %dw 2.0
        output application/json
        ---
        {
          employee: {
            id: payload.employeeId,
            personalInfo: {
              firstName: payload.firstName,
              lastName: payload.lastName,
              email: lower(payload.email),
              phone: payload.phoneNumber
            },
            employment: {
              department: payload.dept,
              position: payload.jobTitle,
              startDate: payload.startDate as Date,
              manager: payload.managerName
            },
            metadata: {
              requestId: attributes.headers["X-Request-ID"],
              timestamp: now(),
              source: "flex-gateway"
            }
          }
        }
    responseTransformation:
      "enabled": true
      "expression": |
        %dw 2.0
        output application/json
        ---
        {
          success: true,
          employeeId: payload.id,
          onboardingStatus: payload.status,
          nextSteps: payload.pendingTasks,
          estimatedCompletion: payload.estimatedCompletion,
          metadata: {
            processedAt: now(),
            gateway: "flex-gateway"
          }
        }
    errorHandling:
      "enabled": true
      "logErrors": true
      "continueOnError": false</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Monitoring & Analytics -->
            <div id="monitoring" class="policy-content">
                <h3>📊 Monitoring & Analytics Policies</h3>
                
                <div class="policy-grid">
                    <!-- Analytics -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Analytics & Metrics Collection</h3>
                        <p>Collects detailed analytics and metrics for API usage monitoring and business intelligence.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: analytics-collection
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: analytics
  config:
    "enableAnalytics": true
    "collectRequestData": true
    "collectResponseData": true
    "collectHeaders": true
    "excludeHeaders":
      - "Authorization"
      - "Cookie"
      - "Set-Cookie"
    "customDimensions":
      - name: "department"
        value: "#[payload.department]"
      - name: "user_role"
        value: "#[attributes.headers['X-User-Role']]"
      - name: "api_version"
        value: "#[attributes.headers['API-Version']]"
    "businessEvents":
      - eventName: "employee_created"
        condition: "#[attributes.method == 'POST' and attributes.requestPath contains '/employees']"
        data:
          employeeId: "#[payload.id]"
          department: "#[payload.department]"
          timestamp: "#[now()]"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Health Check -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Health Check</h3>
                        <p>Provides health check endpoints for monitoring service availability and status.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: health-check
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: health-check
  config:
    healthCheckPath: "/health"
    "detailedHealth": true
    "includeUpstreamHealth": true
    "customHealthChecks":
      - name: "database"
        url: "http://employee-db:5432/health"
        "timeout": 5000
        "interval": 30000
      - name: "external-service"
        url: "https://external-api.company.com/status"
        "timeout": 10000
        "interval": 60000
    "responseFormat": |
      {
        "status": "${overallStatus}",
        "timestamp": "${now()}",
        "gateway": "flex-gateway",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "checks": {
          "database": "${databaseStatus}",
          "external-service": "${externalServiceStatus}"
        },
        "uptime": "${uptime}",
        "requestCount": "${requestCount}"
      }</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- OpenTelemetry -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>OpenTelemetry Tracing</h3>
                        <p>Enables distributed tracing using OpenTelemetry standards for comprehensive observability.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: opentelemetry-tracing
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: opentelemetry
  config:
    "enabled": true
    serviceName: "flex-gateway"
    serviceVersion: "1.0.0"
    exporterEndpoint: "http://jaeger-collector:14268/api/traces"
    exporterType: "jaeger"
    "samplingRate": 1.0
    "resourceAttributes":
      service.name: "employee-onboarding-gateway"
      service.namespace: "hr-systems"
      deployment.environment: "production"
    "spanAttributes":
      - name: "http.route"
        value: "#[attributes.requestPath]"
      - name: "user.id"
        value: "#[attributes.headers['X-User-ID']]"
      - name: "tenant.id"
        value: "#[attributes.headers['X-Tenant-ID']]"
    "propagationFormats":
      - "tracecontext"
      - "b3"
      - "jaeger"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Metrics Collection -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>Prometheus Metrics</h3>
                        <p>Exposes Prometheus-compatible metrics for monitoring and alerting systems.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: prometheus-metrics
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: prometheus-metrics
  config:
    metricsPath: "/metrics"
    "enabled": true
    "defaultMetrics": true
    "customMetrics":
      - name: "employee_onboarding_requests_total"
        type: "counter"
        description: "Total number of employee onboarding requests"
        labels:
          - "method"
          - "status_code"
          - "department"
      - name: "employee_onboarding_request_duration"
        type: "histogram"
        description: "Duration of employee onboarding requests"
        buckets: [0.1, 0.5, 1.0, 2.5, 5.0, 10.0]
        labels:
          - "method"
          - "endpoint"
      - name: "active_employee_sessions"
        type: "gauge"
        description: "Number of active employee sessions"
        labels:
          - "department"</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Compliance Policies -->
            <div id="compliance" class="policy-content">
                <h3>⚖️ Compliance & Regulatory Policies</h3>
                
                <div class="policy-grid">
                    <!-- GDPR Compliance -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>GDPR Data Protection</h3>
                        <p>Ensures GDPR compliance with data protection, consent management, and privacy controls.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: gdpr-compliance
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: gdpr-protection
  config:
    dataSubjectRights:
      "enabled": true
      "rightToAccess": true
      "rightToRectification": true
      "rightToErasure": true
      "rightToPortability": true
    "consentManagement":
      "required": true
      consentHeader: "X-GDPR-Consent"
      "validConsentValues":
        - "granted"
        - "explicit"
    dataMinimization:
      "enabled": true
      "allowedFields":
        - "firstName"
        - "lastName"
        - "email"
        - "department"
      "restrictedFields":
        - "ssn"
        - "personalId"
        - "bankAccount"
    auditLogging:
      "enabled": true
      "logDataAccess": true
      "logDataModification": true
      "logConsentChanges": true
      retentionPeriod: "7y"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- HIPAA Compliance -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>HIPAA Healthcare Compliance</h3>
                        <p>Implements HIPAA-compliant security measures for healthcare data protection.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: hipaa-compliance
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: healthcare-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: hipaa-security
  config:
    "encryption":
      inTransit: "AES256"
      atRest: "AES256"
      keyRotation: "90d"
    "accessControls":
      minimumAuthentication: "two-factor"
      "sessionTimeout": 900
      "automaticLogoff": true
      "roleBasedAccess": true
    auditControls:
      "enabled": true
      "logAllAccess": true
      "logFailedAttempts": true
      "alertOnSuspiciousActivity": true
      retentionPeriod: "6y"
    "dataIntegrity":
      "checksumValidation": true
      "digitallySigned": true
      "immutableLogs": true
    "businessAssociate":
      "requireBAA": true
      "validateBAACertificate": true
    emergencyAccess:
      "enabled": true
      "breakGlassAccess": true
      emergencyLogLevel: "detailed"</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- PCI DSS Compliance -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>PCI DSS Payment Security</h3>
                        <p>Ensures PCI DSS compliance for payment card data security and handling.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: pci-compliance
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: payment-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: pci-dss-security
  config:
    dataProtection:
      maskPAN: true
      maskCVV: true
      tokenizeCardData: true
      encryptionStandard: "AES256"
    networkSecurity:
      requireTLS: "1.2+"
      restrictedNetworks:
        - "192.168.100.0/24"  # PCI network
      firewallRequired: true
    accessControl:
      uniqueUserIDs: true
      strongPasswords: true
      twoFactorAuth: true
      restrictDefaultPasswords: true
    vulnerabilityManagement:
      regularScans: true
      patchManagement: true
      antivirusRequired: true
    monitoring:
      "logAllAccess": true
      realTimeMonitoring: true
      fileIntegrityMonitoring: true
      alerting:
        "enabled": true
        suspiciousActivity: true
        dataAccess: true</div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- SOX Compliance -->
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <h3>SOX Financial Compliance</h3>
                        <p>Implements Sarbanes-Oxley Act compliance controls for financial data integrity.</p>

                        <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: sox-compliance
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: financial-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: sox-controls
  config:
    internalControls:
      segregationOfDuties: true
      approvalWorkflows: true
      financialReporting: true
      changeManagement: true
    auditTrail:
      "enabled": true
      "immutableLogs": true
      detailedLogging: true
      retentionPeriod: "7y"
      realTimeAlerting: true
    "dataIntegrity":
      "checksumValidation": true
      "digitallySigned": true
      preventUnauthorizedChanges: true
      backupVerification: true
    "accessControls":
      "roleBasedAccess": true
      principleOfLeastPrivilege: true
      regularAccessReviews: true
      privilegedAccountManagement: true
    reporting:
      automaticReporting: true
      exceptionReporting: true
      managementCertification: true
      quarterlyReviews: true</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Advanced Enterprise Policies -->
        <div class="card">
            <h2>🏢 Advanced Enterprise Policies</h2>
            
            <div class="policy-grid">
                <!-- Request Size Limiting -->
                <div class="policy-card">
                    <h3>Request Size Limiting</h3>
                    <p>Controls maximum request payload size to prevent DoS attacks and resource exhaustion.</p>

                    <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: request-size-limiting
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: request-size-limiting
  config:
    maximumRequestSize: 10485760  # 10MB
    rejectMessage: |
      {
        "error": "Request Too Large",
        "message": "Request payload exceeds maximum allowed size of 10MB",
        "maxSizeAllowed": "10MB",
        "timestamp": "${now()}"
      }
    includeHeaders: true
    logViolations: true</div>
                </div>

                <!-- Response Caching -->
                <div class="policy-card">
                    <h3>Response Caching</h3>
                    <p>Caches API responses to improve performance and reduce backend load.</p>

                    <div class="yaml-block">apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: response-caching
  namespace: default
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-lookup-api
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: response-caching
  config:
    cachingStrategy: "TIME_TO_LIVE"
    defaultTTL: 300  # 5 minutes
    maxCacheSize: 100  # MB
    cachingKeyExpression: "#[attributes.requestPath ++ '?department=' ++ attributes.queryParams['department']]"
    responseCachingConditions:
      - statusCode: 200
        condition: "#[attributes.method == 'GET']"
      - statusCode: 201
        "condition": false
    invalidatePatterns:
      - "/api/employees/*"
      - "/api/departments/*"
    cacheHeaders:
      - "Cache-Control"
      - "ETag"
      - "Last-Modified"</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Complete Deployment Example -->
        <div class="card">
            <h2>🚀 Complete Deployment Example</h2>
            
            <div class="config-example">
                <h4>Employee Onboarding Production Configuration</h4>
                <p>Complete production-ready configuration with all essential policies for the employee onboarding platform.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="yaml-block"># Complete Employee Onboarding Gateway Configuration
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: Gateway
metadata:
  name: employee-onboarding-gateway
  namespace: production
spec:
  gatewayClassName: flex
  listeners:
  - name: https
    port: 443
    protocol: HTTPS
    tls:
      mode: Terminate
      certificateRefs:
      - name: employee-onboarding-tls
        kind: Secret

---
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: HTTPRoute
metadata:
  name: employee-onboarding-routes
  namespace: production
spec:
  parentRefs:
  - name: employee-onboarding-gateway
  rules:
  - matches:
    - path:
        type: PathPrefix
        value: /api/employees
    backendRefs:
    - name: employee-service
      port: 80
  - matches:
    - path:
        type: PathPrefix
        value: /api/onboarding
    backendRefs:
    - name: onboarding-service
      port: 80

---
# Security Policies
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: security-stack
  namespace: production
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-routes
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: jwt-validation
  config:
    "jwtKeyOrigin": jwks
    jwksUrl: "https://auth.company.com/.well-known/jwks.json"
    audience: "employee-onboarding-api"
    issuer: "https://auth.company.com/"

---
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: rate-limiting-production
  namespace: production
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-routes
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: rate-limiting
  config:
    "rateLimits":
      - maximumRequests: 1000
        "timePeriod": 1
        "timePeriodTimeUnit": MINUTE
    "quotas":
      - maximumRequests: 100000
        "timePeriod": 1
        "timePeriodTimeUnit": DAY

---
# Monitoring and Analytics
apiVersion: gateway.mulesoft.com/v1alpha1
kind: PolicyBinding
metadata:
  name: monitoring-stack
  namespace: production
spec:
  targetRef:
    name: employee-onboarding-routes
    kind: HTTPRoute
  policyRef:
    name: analytics
  config:
    "enableAnalytics": true
    "collectRequestData": true
    "collectResponseData": true</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Implementation Roadmap Section -->
        <div id="implementation-roadmap" class="card" style="display: none;">
            <h2>🗺️ Implementation Roadmap</h2>
            <div class="config-example">
                <h4>Phased Approach for Flex Gateway Policy Implementation</h4>
                <p>A structured roadmap for implementing comprehensive Flex Gateway policies in enterprise environments with HIPAA compliance and disaster recovery capabilities.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="deployment-grid">
                <div class="policy-card">
                    <h3>Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1-4)</h3>
                    <h4>🔒 Core Security Implementation</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>TLS/SSL Configuration:</strong> Implement HTTPS enforcement and certificate management</li>
                        <li><strong>JWT Authentication:</strong> Set up JWT validation with JWKS integration</li>
                        <li><strong>OAuth 2.0 Enforcement:</strong> Configure OAuth token introspection and validation</li>
                        <li><strong>CORS Policies:</strong> Configure cross-origin resource sharing for web applications</li>
                        <li><strong>IP Filtering:</strong> Implement allowlist/blocklist for network security</li>
                        <li><strong>Basic Audit Logging:</strong> Set up request/response logging with PII protection</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4>📊 Basic Monitoring</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Health Checks:</strong> Implement basic health monitoring endpoints</li>
                        <li><strong>Message Logging:</strong> Configure request/response logging with PII masking</li>
                        <li><strong>Error Handling:</strong> Set up standardized error response formats</li>
                        <li><strong>Basic Metrics:</strong> Configure Prometheus metrics collection</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="config-example">
                        <strong>Deliverables:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Basic security policy configurations</li>
                            <li>Health check endpoints functional</li>
                            <li>Logging framework with HIPAA compliance</li>
                            <li>Initial policy documentation</li>
                            <li>Security testing validation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-card">
                    <h3>Phase 2: Traffic Management (Weeks 5-8)</h3>
                    <h4>🚦 Rate Limiting & Control</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Rate Limiting:</strong> Implement sophisticated rate limiting with sliding windows</li>
                        <li><strong>Spike Control:</strong> Configure traffic spike protection and queuing mechanisms</li>
                        <li><strong>Circuit Breaker:</strong> Set up failure detection and cascading failure prevention</li>
                        <li><strong>Load Balancing:</strong> Implement traffic distribution across multiple backends</li>
                        <li><strong>Request Size Limiting:</strong> Prevent DoS attacks through payload size control</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>🛡️ Threat Protection</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>JSON Threat Protection:</strong> Validate JSON payload structure and limits</li>
                        <li><strong>XML Threat Protection:</strong> Implement XML security validation for SOAP services</li>
                        <li><strong>Schema Validation:</strong> Enforce request/response schema compliance</li>
                        <li><strong>Header Security:</strong> Implement security header injection and sensitive header removal</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="config-example">
                        <strong>Deliverables:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Traffic management policies deployed</li>
                            <li>Threat protection configurations active</li>
                            <li>Performance optimization settings tuned</li>
                            <li>Load testing validation completed</li>
                            <li>Capacity planning documentation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-card">
                    <h3>Phase 3: Advanced Features (Weeks 9-12)</h3>
                    <h4>🔄 Data Transformation</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>DataWeave Transformation:</strong> Implement complex payload transformations</li>
                        <li><strong>Content-Based Routing:</strong> Route requests based on payload content and headers</li>
                        <li><strong>API Versioning:</strong> Implement version management and backward compatibility</li>
                        <li><strong>Response Caching:</strong> Implement intelligent caching for performance optimization</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>📈 Advanced Monitoring</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>OpenTelemetry Tracing:</strong> Implement distributed tracing across services</li>
                        <li><strong>Advanced Analytics:</strong> Configure business event tracking and custom metrics</li>
                        <li><strong>Dashboard Integration:</strong> Connect with Grafana and monitoring systems</li>
                        <li><strong>Alert Management:</strong> Set up intelligent alerting and escalation</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="config-example">
                        <strong>Deliverables:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Transformation policies functional</li>
                            <li>Advanced monitoring dashboard operational</li>
                            <li>Caching configurations optimized</li>
                            <li>Analytics and reporting systems active</li>
                            <li>Performance benchmarks documented</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-card">
                    <h3>Phase 4: Compliance & Governance (Weeks 13-16)</h3>
                    <h4>⚖️ Regulatory Compliance</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>GDPR Compliance:</strong> Implement comprehensive data protection and consent management</li>
                        <li><strong>HIPAA Security:</strong> Configure healthcare data protection with audit controls</li>
                        <li><strong>PCI DSS:</strong> Set up payment card data security and tokenization</li>
                        <li><strong>SOX Controls:</strong> Implement financial data integrity and segregation controls</li>
                        <li><strong>Multi-Tenant Security:</strong> Configure tenant isolation and data segregation</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>🏢 Enterprise Governance</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Policy Orchestration:</strong> Implement advanced multi-policy combinations</li>
                        <li><strong>Zero Trust Architecture:</strong> Deploy comprehensive zero trust security patterns</li>
                        <li><strong>Compliance Automation:</strong> Set up automated compliance monitoring and reporting</li>
                        <li><strong>Audit Framework:</strong> Implement comprehensive audit logging and retention</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="config-example">
                        <strong>Deliverables:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>All compliance policies configured and validated</li>
                            <li>Audit logging framework comprehensive</li>
                            <li>Governance documentation complete</li>
                            <li>Compliance validation reports generated</li>
                            <li>Risk assessment completed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Next Steps Section -->
        <div id="next-steps" class="card" style="display: none;">
            <h2>⏭️ Next Steps & Action Items</h2>
            <div class="config-example">
                <h4>Immediate Actions & Long-term Strategy</h4>
                <p>Prioritized action items for successful Flex Gateway policy implementation and ongoing management with enterprise-grade security and compliance.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="deployment-grid">
                <div class="policy-card">
                    <h3>🔥 Immediate Actions (Next 30 Days)</h3>
                    <h4>Critical Security Implementation</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Environment Setup:</strong> Deploy Flex Gateway instances across all environments</li>
                        <li><strong>TLS Configuration:</strong> Implement HTTPS enforcement with proper certificate management</li>
                        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Configure JWT validation and OAuth 2.0 token enforcement</li>
                        <li><strong>Basic Rate Limiting:</strong> Implement initial traffic control policies</li>
                        <li><strong>Health Monitoring:</strong> Set up basic health check endpoints</li>
                        <li><strong>Audit Logging:</strong> Configure comprehensive request/response logging</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4>Compliance Foundation</h4>
                    <ul>
